<subSubSection pageId="18" pageNumber="35" type="type species">
<paragraph pageId="18" pageNumber="35">Type species.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="18" pageNumber="35">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fairmaire &amp; Germain" authorityYear="1858" class="Hexapoda" family="Buprestidae" genus="Anthaxia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cupriceps">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="35">Anthaxia cupriceps</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Fairmaire &amp; Germain, 1858 by original designation.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="18" pageNumber="35">
The genus was originally described by 
<bibRefCitation author="Holynski, R" journalOrPublisher="Elytron, Barcelona," pageId="28" pageNumber="45" pagination="163 - 167" refId="B25" refString="Holynski, R, 1989. The content and systematic position of Cylindrophora Solier, 1851 (Coleoptera, Buprestidae). Elytron, Barcelona, 3: 163 - 167" title="The content and systematic position of Cylindrophora Solier, 1851 (Coleoptera, Buprestidae)." volume="3" year="1989">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Hołyński">Holynski</normalizedToken>
(1989)
</bibRefCitation>
as a subgenus of 
<taxonomicName class="Hexapoda" family="Buprestidae" genus="Anthaxia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="35">Anthaxia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and it was upgraded to the genus level by 
<bibRefCitation author="Bily, S" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="27" pageNumber="44" pagination="1 - 11" refId="B12" refString="Bily, S, 2004. Taxonomic studies on Anthaxiina Gory &amp; Laporte de Castelnau and Curina Holynski (Coleoptera: Buprestidae). Zootaxa 555: 1 - 11" title="Taxonomic studies on Anthaxiina Gory &amp; Laporte de Castelnau and Curina Holynski (Coleoptera: Buprestidae)." volume="555" year="2004">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Bílý">Bily</normalizedToken>
(2004)
</bibRefCitation>
. According to 
<bibRefCitation author="Bellamy, CL" journalOrPublisher="Folia Heyrovskyana, Supplementum" pageId="27" pageNumber="44" refId="B3" refString="Bellamy, CL, 2008. A world catalogue and bibliography of the jewel beetles (Coleoptera: Buprestoidea). Volume 3. Buprestinae: Pterobothrini through Agrilinae: Rhaeboscelina. Pensoft series faunistica No. 78, Sofia - Moscow, pp. (1-2) + 1261-1932." title="A world catalogue and bibliography of the jewel beetles (Coleoptera: Buprestoidea). Volume 3. Buprestinae: Pterobothrini through Agrilinae: Rhaeboscelina. Pensoft series faunistica No. 78, Sofia - Moscow, pp. (1 - 2) + 1261 - 1932." year="2008">Bellamy (2008)</bibRefCitation>
it contains 18 species but the division to several subgenera is necessary. Three species were transferred to the separate, monotypic genera (
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bílý" authorityYear="2013" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Charlesina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="35">Charlesina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
gen. n., 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bílý" authorityYear="2013" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Cobosina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="35">Cobosina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
gen. n. and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bílý" authorityYear="2013" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Marikia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="35">Marikia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
gen. n. - see above), the remaining 15 species is assigned into three subgenera.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
